  "description": "You literally move through time. blend starts at 0.1 — deep in the past, sound arriving through long grain reconstruction, the present barely audible beneath the memory layer. Mod wheel is the temporal lever: drag it forward and blend rises toward 0.95, the past collapsing, the perception engine taking over, the sound becoming immediate and present. At full wheel you are entirely in now — memoryGrain has shrunk to near real-time, reactivity at maximum. The instrument has transformed. Release the wheel and time reverses: the past reasserts itself slowly, notes once again arriving as echoes of themselves, the present dissolving into memory. Aftertouch maximizes interference at any temporal position — the boundary between states becoming unstable, resonant. Velocity controls reactivity — how quickly both states respond to your playing.",
